= 2 August 1915\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19150802.2.8.2\n| accessdate = 10 August 2019}}</ref>\n| away = City\n| try1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]], Warner\n| con1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = Mincham\n| con2 = [[Ernie Asher]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park\n| attendance = 4,000\n| referee = A Ferguson\n}}\n\n==Roope Rooster Knockout competition==\nNewton, Grafton and North Shore were round 1 victors and North Shore received a bye meaning they should have advanced to the final directly. However Grafton and Newton played out a 2\u20132 draw in their semi-final. Rather than play a replay the league decided to have a second semi-final match between Grafton and North Shore, with Newton progressing to the final. North Shore beat Grafton and then defeated Newton in the final the win the inaugural Roope Rooster trophy which is still played for today.\n===Round 1===\n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 9 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = Grafton\n| score = 13\u20139\n| report =<ref name=\"initial_round\">{{cite news\n| title =Roope's Rooster/The Initial Round/Grafton Defeats Ponsonby/City's Poor Exhibition/Newton's Easy Win\n| page =4\n| publisher = New Zealand Herald, Volume LII, Issue 15991\n| date = 11 August 1915\n| url =https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/NZH19150809.2.11.1\n| accessdate = 12 August 2019}}</ref>| away = Ponsonby\n| try1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 3\n| con1 = [[Karl Ifwersen]] 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = D Corby, S Jones, F McWhirter\n| con2 =\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Victoria Park # 1\n| attendance = 3,000\n| referee = Calthorpe\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| date = 9 August\n| time = 3:00\n| home = North Shore\n| score = 16\u20138\n| report =<ref name=\"initial_round\" />| away = City\n| try1 = T Paul 2, Fife, Anderson\n| con1 = Jack Paul 2\n| pen1 =\n| try2 = B Tresize, Avery\n| con2 = [[Albert Asher]]\n| pen2 =\n| stadium = Devonport Domain # 1\n| attendance =\n| referee = Fielding\n}}\n \n{{rugbybox collapsible\n| da